Eugene BASTIDA v. The UNITED STATES of America. No. 9010. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Oct. 10, 1938. Fred McDonald, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., of San Francisco, Cal.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed; that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issue forthwith.
